history.content: In general, most EECS classes do not enforce prerequisites when enrolling. However, sometimes, like this semester, when overenrolled people without prerequisites will be removed first. But, since you're not CS (and presumably not EECS), you'd also be first on the chopping block regardless so enrollment-wise it shouldn't matter too much.

For CS 189 I know that one of the prerequisites is Math 53. Does anyone know if Cal Central will still let me register for the class regardless of not having that prerequisite? I’ve completed Math 54 and CS 70, the other two prerequisites. Also, how much of that class focuses on the material from Math 53? I am not a CS major.
history.subject: CS 189 Prerequisite
